      <topic id="PHP95819" outputclass="indicationsAndDose" rev="1.21">
        <title>Indications and dose</title>
        <body>
          <section outputclass="indicationAndDoseGroup">
            <sectiondiv outputclass="therapeuticIndications">
              <p outputclass="therapeuticIndication">Mobilise lower respiratory tract secretions in mucous consolidation (e.g. cystic fibrosis)</p>
              <p outputclass="therapeuticIndication">Mild to moderate acute viral bronchiolitis in infants</p>
            </sectiondiv>
            <p outputclass="routesOfAdministration">By inhalation of nebulised solution</p>
            <ul outputclass="patientGroups">
              <li outputclass="patientGroup adult">
                <p>Adult</p>
                <p>4 mL 2–4 times a day, temporary irritation, such as coughing, hoarseness, or reversible bronchoconstriction may occur; an inhaled bronchodilator can be used before treatment with hypertonic sodium chloride to reduce the risk of these adverse effects.</p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </body>
      </topic>
